result.execSummary:
All charges against Korbel Ison Gray in this case have been dismissed. These charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Korbel Ison Gray is presumed innocent.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

04:25 PM Attorney Jade K Hall in court, defendant Korbel Ison Gray not in court, in custody.  Abby Rockendorf appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  PARTIES APPEAR BY VIDEO.
Case set for a preliminary hearing. States witness is not present. Defense moves to dismiss. Court ordered case dismissed without prejudice.

Attorney Jade K Hall in court, was present by video prior to the case being called on the record. Defendant Korbel Ison Gray not in court, in custody.  Gregg Herman appeared in person for the State of Wisconsin.   
Case set for a preliminary hearing. State witness was not present. Court ordered case adjourned for CAUSE for a Preliminary Hearing in Preliminary Hearing Court, Room 146 of the Criminal Justice Facility.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for July 7, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION Level 5.

Defendant Korbel Ison Gray in court with attorney Darryl Everett Smith.  Defendant Korbel Ison Gray in custody.  Anthony J Moore appeared for the State of Wisconsin.    All parties appeared by video conference.
  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Sanders, Branch 28. Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold the defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL.

Preliminary hearing scheduled for June 8, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
